			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> keynote:</span><br><i>Model-Driven Engineering Meets Generic Language Technology</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MarkvandenBrand.html">Mark van den Brand</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_2">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_2</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagM">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly connects model-driven engineering with generic language technology, arguing for cross-pollination of concepts and tooling.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It surveys and leverages generic language tools (e.g., parsing, analysis frameworks) as infrastructure for MDE.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It discusses using language-technology-based mappings/transformations to support MDE scenarios.
</li></ul></li></ul>
